headline: Nike China Pressures Deepen As Pou Sheng Hit Tests Valuation
summary: Pou Sheng, a key distributor for NIKE in China, has reported a sharp profit drop, raising questions about consumer demand and inventory conditions. Analysts are flagging the possibility that NIKE could announce a major restructuring program in China as it reassesses its approach in this core market. The situation highlights potential pressure on NIKE's China distribution model and how the company manages product flow and demand signals with partners. NIKE, traded as NYSE:NKE, is...
